item.title: By: Ben
item.dc:creator: Ben
item.description: You're welcome! I'm really glad it helped! And to your question, D2 at move 42 is not as good because it gives Black more forcing moves later on. And also, since Lee Sedol was one of the first professionals I really started following, I am rooting for him; but to be honest, I've come to really admire Gu Li's kiai and style of play, so I have no idea who will actually win. =)
item.content:encoded: You’re welcome! I’m really glad it helped! And to your question, D2 at move 42 is not as good because it gives Black more forcing moves later on. And also, since Lee Sedol was one of the first professionals I really started following, I am rooting for him; but to be honest, I’ve come to really admire Gu Li’s kiai and style of play, so I have no idea who will actually win. =)
